From 953cc07189d0f334bc0ef930ee38e51ecf90993e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 08:29:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Accept CSS Text 4 text-align:justify-all and the
 text-align-last property

text-align gains the shorthand value justify-all (justifies the last line as
well), and text-align-last (auto | start | end | left | right | center |
justify | match-parent) is a new inherited longhand.  The value validator
previously dropped text-align:justify-all as invalid and, while text-align-last
survived via the default-accept path, it was not in the inherited-property set.
Accept justify-all and validate text-align-last explicitly, and mark
text-align-last inherited so getComputedStyle resolves it on descendants.
